text: Elicia Marshall (born September 3, 1979) is a former synchronized swimmer from the United States. Elicia competed in the women's team event at the 2000 Summer Olympics, finishing in fifth place. == References == Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:American synchronized swimmers Category:Olympic synchronized swimmers of the United States Category:Synchronized swimmers at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists
